Class DebuggingInferencer

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Inferencer

    final class DebuggingInferencer
extends ForwardingInferencer
    An Inferencer decorator that logs method calls and checks they respect the Inferencer API and lifecycle.

    This decorator is used for debugging purposes. It logs method invocations (at DEBUG level) using a supplied Logger and checks preconditions concerning both method parameters and invocation order w.r.t. the prescribed Inferencer lifecycle.

      • getConfigurationDigest

        public String getConfigurationDigest()
        Returns a string digest depending on any configuration parameter that may determine a change in the entailments produced by the engine. This method serves to detect when, after a change in the configuration of the inference engine (e.g., a change of configured inference rules), the already computed closure becomes invalid and has thus to be recomputed. This method is not supposed to throw exceptions. Delegates, checking the invocation respects the inferencer lifecycle.
        Specified by:
        getConfigurationDigest in interface Inferencer
        Overrides:
        getConfigurationDigest in class ForwardingInferencer
        Returns:
        the computed string signature

      • newSession

        public Inferencer.Session newSession(String id,
                            ClosureStatus closureStatus,
                            Inferencer.Context context)
                              throws org.openrdf.repository.RepositoryException
        Creates a new Inferencer.Session for the read or read/write transaction currently active. Parameter writable specifies whether the underlying transaction and connection object are modifiable, while parameter currentClosureStatus specifies the status of the closure currently materialized in the repository. Delegates and logs, wrapping the returned Session so to log and check method calls and checking that the method invocation respects the inferencer lifecycle.
        Specified by:
        newSession in interface Inferencer
        Overrides:
        newSession in class ForwardingInferencer
        Parameters:
        id - a parameter identifying the session (e.g., for logging purposes), typically related to the transaction it is associated to
        closureStatus - the status of the closure currently materialized in the repository
        context - a context object providing read/write (if writable) access to data in the repository
        Returns:
        the created Inferencer.Session
        Throws:
        org.openrdf.repository.RepositoryException - in case the creation failed, for any reason
